Polimetric
==========

This project reuses code and design from Demograph and is built on the same
upstream historical datasets. Attribution below is carried forward from
Demograph's NOTICE and extended.

Everything this project itself creates — code, the visualization, and any
derived datasets — is offered freely. Choose a project LICENSE (CC0 1.0 matches
the upstream code and imposes no conditions). Note, however, that some upstream
DATA sources are licensed CC BY and DO ask for credit even when your own
additions do not. Please keep the attributions below when you reuse the data.


Code & framing
--------------
Demograph — https://github.com/alexandrosm/Demograph
  Dedicated to the public domain under CC0 1.0. Pipeline and D3 rendering reused
  here; no permission or attribution legally required, credited as good practice.


Data sources
------------
HYDE 3.2.1 — gridded population reconstruction
  https://doi.org/10.17026/dans-25g-gez3
  Licensed CC BY. Credit required on reuse of the data.

Cliopatria (Seshat Global History Databank) — historical border polygons
  https://github.com/Seshat-Global-History-Databank/cliopatria
  Licensed CC BY. Credit required on reuse of the data.

Natural Earth — modern country / region boundaries
  https://www.naturalearthdata.com/
  Public domain. No attribution required; credited as good practice.


Original work referenced
-------------------------
John B. Sparks, "Histomap" (1931). Conceptual ancestor only; not reproduced
here.


Raw data is not committed to this repository (see .gitignore). Download HYDE via
the pipeline and place Cliopatria and Natural Earth in data/raw/ before
rebuilding. Only processed outputs (data/processed/, web/*.js) are tracked.
